{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_12","type":"agent_message","text":"## Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job for `io.vertx:vertx-docgen:0.9.4` failed during test generation/post-generation. Preserved work is available at https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7782-library-new-request-io.vertx-vertx-docgen-0.9.4-8b9eb80f.\n\nThe generated tests exercised `ToolProvider.getSystemJavaCompiler()` at native runtime. `nativeTest` built the image but all four tests failed when embedded `javac` initialized `com.sun.tools.javac.file.Locations` (`NullPointerException` in `UnixFileSystem.getPath`, followed by `NoClassDefFoundError`). The post-generation step removed the entire runtime-compiler test suite, leaving no generated test source; the metrics confirm failure after 6 iterations with 0 generated LOC and 0% coverage. No usable dynamic-access coverage was produced.\n\nInspect:\n- `logs/io.vertx:vertx-docgen:0.9.4/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-07-14T00-12-50-124674Z.log`\n- `logs/io.vertx:vertx-docgen:0.9.4/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-07-14T00-13-55-917158Z.log`\n- `logs/io.vertx:vertx-docgen:0.9.4/metadata-fix/codex.log`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Review the preserved generated test and metadata work, and reproduce the native failure.\n2. Determine whether `vertx-docgen` has a meaningful native-safe test path that avoids runtime Java compilation.\n3. Add and validate that test with `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.vertx:vertx-docgen:0.9.4`, or decide whether this library requires an explicit coverage exception."}}
